4:["$","div",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-[#09090b] text-gray-100 antialiased","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"fixed inset-0 pointer-events-none","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"absolute top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[800px] h-[600px] bg-green-500/5 rounded-full blur-[120px]"}]}],["$","nav",null,{"className":"relative max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-6 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","$Ld",null,{"href":"/","className":"flex items-center gap-2","children":[["$","svg",null,{"className":"w-5 h-5","fill":"none","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","strokeWidth":1.5,"stroke":"currentColor","children":["$","path",null,{"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","d":"M9 12.75 11.25 15 15 9.75m-3-7.036A11.959 11.959 0 0 1 3.598 6 11.99 11.99 0 0 0 3 9.749c0 5.592 3.824 10.29 9 11.623 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.31-.21-2.571-.598-3.751h-.152c-3.196 0-6.1-1.248-8.25-3.285Z"}]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-bold text-lg tracking-tight","children":"ClawDoctor"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-6 text-sm text-gray-400","children":[["$","$Ld",null,{"href":"/#monitors","className":"hover:text-white transition","children":"Monitors"}],["$","$Ld",null,{"href":"/#pricing","className":"hover:text-white transition","children":"Pricing"}],["$","$Ld",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"hover:text-white transition","children":"Blog"}],["$","$Ld",null,{"href":"/docs","className":"hover:text-white transition","children":"Docs"}]]}]]}],["$","main",null,{"className":"relative max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 pt-10 pb-24","children":[["$","$Ld",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-300 transition mb-10","children":"← All posts"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 text-xs text-gray-500 mb-5","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-03-15","children":"2026-03-15"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"·"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"4 min read"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold leading-tight mb-10 text-white","children":"Why I Built ClawDoctor: A Self-Healing Monitor for Local AI Gateways"}],["$","article",null,{"className":"prose-custom","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["I run twenty-something OpenClaw agents in production."]}],["$","p","1",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["Not a side project. Not a toy. These agents generate content, process customer data, and drive revenue. When they break, money stops moving and customers notice."]}],["$","p","2",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["For the first six months, I dealt with failures the way most people do: I found out from a user, or I woke up to a notification that something downstream had gone quiet. I would SSH in, grep logs, figure out that the gateway had died two hours ago, restart it, and go back to sleep. Every time I told myself I'd set up proper monitoring. Every time, something more urgent came up."]}],["$","h2","3",{"className":"text-xl font-bold text-white mt-10 mb-4","children":"The night that changed it"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["It was a Tuesday, around 3am. I got a message from a client: \"the daily briefing didn't arrive.\" That briefing was generated by a cron job that ran at midnight, posted results through an OpenClaw session, and delivered via webhook. Somewhere in that chain, the gateway had silently died at 11:58pm, two minutes before the cron fired."]}],["$","p","5",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["The cron ran. It connected to localhost:8080. It got a connection refused. It exited with code 0 because the error handling was too lenient. No alert fired. No log was written. The cron technically \"succeeded.\""]}],"$Le","$Lf","$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18","$L19","$L1a","$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f","$L20"]}],"$L21"]}],"$L22"]}]
e:["$","p","6",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["I restarted the gateway, re-ran the job, delivered the briefing with an apology. Four hours of silence. I had been asleep."]}]
f:["$","p","7",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["That was the moment I decided to stop tolerating it."]}]
10:["$","h2","8",{"className":"text-xl font-bold text-white mt-10 mb-4","children":"What I wanted didn't exist"}]
11:["$","p","9",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["I looked around for tools that could watch OpenClaw specifically. Sentry handles errors in application code. Langfuse handles LLM call tracing. Uptime monitors handle HTTP endpoints. None of them understood OpenClaw's state files, session structure, or cron delivery model. None of them knew how to look at an OpenClaw gateway and say: this restarted three times in the last hour, something is wrong."]}]
12:["$","p","10",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["I didn't want a generic monitoring dashboard with fifty knobs to configure. I wanted something opinionated: a process that understood OpenClaw and knew what \"healthy\" looked like, without me having to teach it from scratch."]}]
13:["$","h2","11",{"className":"text-xl font-bold text-white mt-10 mb-4","children":"Building the first version"}]
14:["$","p","12",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["The first version was a Node script I ran in a tmux session. It polled the OpenClaw process table every sixty seconds, checked the gateway port, read the session logs. If the gateway was down, it ran ",["$","code","1",{"className":"text-green-400/80 bg-green-400/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm font-mono","children":"openclaw gateway restart"}]," and sent me a Telegram message."]}]
15:["$","p","13",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["That alone saved me probably three incidents in the first two weeks."]}]
16:["$","p","14",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["Then I added cron watching. OpenClaw cron jobs write delivery receipts (or they're supposed to). If a receipt is missing, ClawDoctor flags it. If it's stale, ClawDoctor flags it. You get a message that says: \"writer-content-drafts last delivery was 26 hours ago, expected every 24h.\""]}]
17:["$","p","15",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["Then session watching. Sessions that run more than 3x their baseline duration. Sessions that emit repeated errors. Sessions that start and never finish."]}]
18:["$","p","16",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["Then cost watching. A runaway session burning $40 in a loop is not a hypothetical. It has happened to me and I caught it too late."]}]
19:["$","h2","17",{"className":"text-xl font-bold text-white mt-10 mb-4","children":"Where it is now"}]
1a:["$","p","18",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["ClawDoctor is a proper daemon now. It starts on boot, runs five watchers on configurable intervals, and maintains a local event log. The free tier covers the core watchers. Paid tiers add pattern matching, multi-channel alerts, and in v2, actual auto-fix actions: token refresh, config repair, approval flows via Telegram before taking any risky action."]}]
1b:["$","p","19",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["The auto-restart feature has been running in production for four months. In that time, it has restarted my gateway eleven times. I noticed zero of those restarts while they were happening."]}]
1c:["$","h2","20",{"className":"text-xl font-bold text-white mt-10 mb-4","children":"Who this is for"}]
1d:["$","p","21",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["If you're running one OpenClaw agent locally, you probably don't need ClawDoctor yet. When it breaks, you'll notice immediately."]}]
1e:["$","p","22",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["If you're running several agents, crons, and sessions (in production, for paying customers, overnight), you need something watching the watcher. That's what ClawDoctor is."]}]
1f:["$","p","23",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["It's open source. The core is free. Install it in sixty seconds with ",["$","code","1",{"className":"text-green-400/80 bg-green-400/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm font-mono","children":"npm install -g clawdoctor && clawdoctor init"}],"."]}]
20:["$","p","24",{"className":"text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["The 3am gateway crash that started this: it hasn't happened undetected since."]}]
21:["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-white/[0.06]","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-gray-500 mb-5","children":"ClawDoctor watches your OpenClaw setup so you don't have to."}],["$","a",null,{"href":"/#install","className":"inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-500 text-white font-medium text-sm rounded-lg transition shadow-lg shadow-green-600/20","children":"Install Free →"}]]}]
